name: Abacavir
description: This medicine is usually taken one (1) time in the morning and one (1) time at night.Abacavir can be taken with or without food.

name: Bortezomib
description: Loss of appetite nausea, or burning, swelling, or a lump under your skin where the needle is placed, Fatigue, Fever

name: Cefixime
description: You may take cefixime with or without food. If you have stomach pain, take cefixime with food.

name: Darunavir (Prezista®)
description: This tablet is usually taken one (1) time each morning and one (1) time each evening.Darunavir should be taken with food.

name: Efavirenz
description: This medicine is taken once a day, usually at bedtime. It must be taken every day.

name: Fidaxomicin
description: Signs of an allergic reaction like fever; itching; seizures; or swelling of face, lips, tongue, or throat.

name: Furosemide
description: Feeling dizzy, Headache, Diarrhea (when taking the liquid medicine),Low blood pressure,

name: Gemtuzumab ozogamicin
description: Flu-like reaction, which may cause fever, chills, headache, shortness of breath, and dizziness

name: Hydralazine
description: Low blood counts with an increased risk of bleeding, infection, and fatigue

name: Immune globulin
description: Muscle and joint pain, nausea and vomiting, plus skin rash (serum sickness)

name: Levothyroxine
description: You should take levothyroxine before breakfast to decrease trouble sleeping at night.

name: Mechlorethamine
description: The doctor may prescribe medicine to keep you from feeling sick and throwing up after you receive mechlorethamine.

name: Melphalan
description: Allergic reaction: symptoms include rash, itching, swelling of the feet or ankles, fast heart beat, or low blood pressure.

name: Metronidazole
description: Take this medicine with or without food. If you have stomach upset, take metronidazole with food.

name: Morphine
description: If you are taking both the fast-acting and long-acting forms of morphine, you may only need to take the for “breakthrough” pain.

name: Nevirapine
description: Rash If you experience any type of rash, stop taking nevirapine right away and call the doctor or nurse.

name: Oxycodone
description: If you are taking oxycodone with acetaminophen, do not take extra acetaminophen (Tylenol®) or medicines containing acetaminophen.

name: Phenytoin
description: You will receive one (1) injection 24 hours after your last dose of chemotherapy.

name: Rivaroxaban
description: You will receive one (1) injection 24 hours after your last dose of chemotherapy. A nurse will give you the medicine
If you are taking oxycodone with acetaminophen, do not take extra acetaminophen (Tylenol®) or medicines containing acetaminophen.
